\title{Slice category}
\taxon{definition}
\import{macros}

\p{The \em{slice} [category](math-000D) #{\cat{C}/X} sliced over an object #{X \in \cat{C}} consists in:}

\ul{
\li{Objects: morphisms #{A \rightarrow X} for some #{A \in \cat{C}}}
\li{Morphisms: #{A\rightarrow B} such that the triangle commutes}
\li{Identities and composition come directly from #{\cat{C}}}}